==Chinese==

===Etymology===
From [[海]] ("sea") + [[笛]] (a transverse bamboo flute).  Possibly derived from Arabic ''ghaita'' or ''rhaita'' (a folk oboe played primarily in North Africa).

===Pronunciation===
*Mandarin
**Pinyin: hǎi dí (hai3 di2)
*Cantonese
**Jyutping:

===Noun===
'''[[海]][[笛]]''' (simplified and traditional)

# the smaller size of ''suona'' (a conical Chinese double reed woodwind instrument with a metal bell, in the oboe or shawm category).

